# API Route Guidelines

## Next.js API Routes
- Use the App Router API pattern with `route.ts` files
- Always export named functions (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.)
- Use `NextRequest` and `NextResponse` types from 'next/server'
- Return properly typed JSON responses with consistent error handling

## Request/Response Types
- Define interfaces for request and response bodies
- Use consistent naming: `interface [Feature][Action]Request` and `interface [Feature][Action]Response`
- Always include a `success: boolean` field in responses
- Include optional `error?: string` field for error responses

## Error Handling
- Use try-catch blocks for all async operations
- Return meaningful error messages to the client
- Log errors with `console.error()` for debugging
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes via NextResponse

## External API Calls
- Include proper User-Agent headers when scraping content
- Handle network errors gracefully
- Validate URLs and inputs before processing
- Use appropriate timeouts for external requests